17. Time Division Multiplexing (TDM)
TDM is a multiplexing technique where multiple signals share a channel using time slots.
Each user gets a fixed time slot
Efficient bandwidth usage
Used in digital communication systems.


18. What is Network?
A network is a collection of connected devices that communicate with each other.
Shares resources
Enables data communication
Example: Internet, LAN


19. What is Wavelength?
Wavelength is the distance between two consecutive peaks of a wave.
Measured in meters
Inversely related to frequency
It is an important property of signals.


20. What is Signal?
A signal is a physical form used to transmit data.
Can be electrical or electromagnetic
Carries information between devices


21. Distance Vector Routing
It is a routing technique where routers share routing information with neighbors.
Uses distance (hop count)
Chooses shortest path
Example: RIP protocol


22. What is Switching?
Switching is the process of transferring data from source to destination through different paths.
Types:
Circuit switching
Packet switching
Message switching
It ensures efficient data delivery.







